Project How To Start Building An Immersive Experience FAQs and important pointers to keep in mind when transforming your model into an immersive experience with Join Discord Preparing your model Taking some extra time to prepare your model will lead to significant improvements in final quality, as well as a reduction in import We√¢¬Ä¬ôve laid out a systematic way to prepare your model For any questions, send us a message on Discord and we√¢¬Ä¬ôll get back to you as soon as possible, normally within the Materials & Lights Making sure that materials and lights are compatible with and look right in a environment is key to ensuring both immersion for users, as well as stability and √¢¬Ä¬ç Material Support Avoid using the following material types as they are not supported: GI override Displacements maps Lights Do not use more than 5 overlapping lights in close proximity as this will significantly degrade For best results: Use area lights instead of many small point lights Lights can be fine tuned after import if they are put on the correct layer (see layer organization section) Layer Organization To ensure that your model is properly prepared for high performance in a environment and faithful to its intended appearance, please ensure that objects are properly sorted into the following layers (or ). √¢¬Ä¬ç Objects with Glass and Transparent Materials In order to reduce import times and optimize for performance, objects with transparency should be organized as following: Objects with simple transparency such as panes of glass on layer TranslucentSimple_[layer name] Complex objects (over triangles) with transparency such as a chandelier on layer TranslucentComplex_[layer name] Plants and Foliage Lights should be collected on a layer called Foliage_[layer name] Lights Plants and foliage should be collected on a layer called Lights_[layer name] Labeling Rooms Palatial can display the name of the room or area you√¢¬Ä¬ôre in, as long as you define the For each area in your model, draw a box best approximating its boundaries (do not use any other shape), and name the object [Room name]. Alternatively, place each box on a separate layer and name the layer after the Objects Similar to setting up a model for rendering, making sure that objects have the correct geometry, normals, and state will go a long way in reducing unexpected Walls Do not use planes as wells, as they will not render Everything must have thickness - we recommend walls be at least thick at room scale, or light may still bleed Overlapping Duplicates If a surface is rapidly flickering when you pan in the model (z-fighting), there may be overlapping Ideally delete the duplicate, however a quick and dirty fix is to slightly move one mesh so they√¢¬Ä¬ôre no longer Unfreeze Unlock Objects Unfreeze unlock all objects that will be exported, or else they will not show up in the Palatial Scene Access Ensure that all parts of the scene can be accessed by individuals walking For example, if there are doors in the model, make sure that they√¢¬Ä¬ôre Setup Design Options Material Support If there are multiple design options or configurations in your model, Palatial allows you to toggle between options To use this feature, group or organize options per layer: Label the first option as Option_A_[RoomName], the second option as Option_B_[RoomName], There is no limit to the number of options you can include Keep in mind that the group or layer must include everything for the option, as only 1 options is visible at a Sign up for Alpha Want to test Palatial out with your project?
